snippet.title: React India 2025 Impressions
snippet.description:
Welcome to React India 2025, where the world‚Äôs most passionate React developers came together in Goa, India ‚Äî and turned a tech conference into an unforgettable celebration of learning, laughter, and community.

From deep-dive workshops and hands-on coding sessions to beachside brainstorms and impromptu coffee-break collaborations ‚Äî this year‚Äôs edition was more than just talks and slides. It was about people. About the global React family that builds, learns, and grows together. üåçüíô

üî• What Made React India 2025 Special

üå¥ Location, vibes, and pure energy ‚Äî A one-of-a-kind developer experience in scenic Goa.

üë©‚Äçüíª 800+ in-person devs and 3,000+ online participants connecting in real time.

üéôÔ∏è 35+ world-class speakers from across the globe ‚Äî sharing insights on React, performance, state management, React Native, and the future of front-end development.

üí° Hands-on workshops, hack sessions & networking ‚Äî where devs built projects, shared ideas, and found collaborators.

üåÖ After-hours fun ‚Äî beach walks, chai talks, music nights, and laughter echoing long after the conference ended.

üí¨ The Community That Built It All

React India 2025 wasn‚Äôt just attended by developers ‚Äî it was powered by them.
From open-source maintainers to first-time attendees, everyone contributed, shared, and made this event truly special.
Every high-five, every spontaneous conversation, every ‚ÄúI follow your work!‚Äù moment ‚Äî reminded us what makes React unique: the people behind the code.

Build an AI-Powered Photo Editor with React

Abstract - Creating image editing applications traditionally requires complex infrastructure, specialized ML expertise, and ongoing maintenance‚Äîmaking it costly and time-consuming for developers to build and scale.

snippet.title: React India 2025 - Day 01
snippet.description:
Join a lineup of frontend leaders as they share practical insights on speeding up frontends, designing framework-friendly components, and delivering scalable experiences. 

Each talk dives into real-world challenges and approaches you can apply today.

Chapters:
41:07 Ashita Prasad ‚Äî Solving the Monolithic Frontend Crisis
1:15:40 Mayank Mahavar ‚Äî Framework Design Lessons: Catalyst core for Users
2:26:32 Ankeet Maini ‚Äî The Story of two World Cups: Streaming World Cups to millions
3:02:46 Naveen Chand ‚Äî Interfaces for Humans and Machines: Designing React component SDKs
3:27:15 Udhayaprakash R V ‚Äî How to Cut load times 10x and slash cost by 50%
5:17:37 Sayantan Mondal ‚Äî Building reusable components for complex data
5:47:22 Nitesh Seram ‚Äî Language-agnostic approaches for modern frontend
6:30:12 Sulagna Shosh ‚Äî The Future of Real-time React

What you‚Äôll learn:
Practical frontend architecture patterns to reduce monolith fallout
Designing reusable, scalable components and SDKs for teams
Strategies to optimize load times and costs at scale
Real-time updates and streaming considerations for large audiences
